# Betting (Remote) - Money Laundering and Terrorist Financing Risk Assessment 2023

**Overall Risk Rating:** High

## Summary

Remote betting operations present high risk for money laundering and terrorist financing due to the lack of physical customer presence, accessibility to multiple accounts, and vulnerabilities in payment systems. The sector faces particular challenges with identity verification, mule accounts, and peer-to-peer betting platforms.

## Inherent Risks by Vulnerability Category

### Operator Control Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| Operators failing to comply with prevention of money laundering and terrorist financing legislation and guidance | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| Operators staking and winning directly and indirectly on their own products | Low (1) | Medium (2) | Low (2) | No change |
| Lack of competence of key personnel and licence holders which can then be exploited by criminals seeking to launder the proceeds of crime | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | Decrease in likelihood |
| Inadequate or lack of 'know your customer' (KYC) checks resulting in criminals laundering criminal proceeds or risk of this occurring | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| 'High value' customer schemes | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | No change |
| High monetary thresholds | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | New risk rating |
| KYC completed at the point of withdrawal | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |
| Third party business relationships and business investors | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |

### Licensing and Integrity Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| Gambling operations run or acquired by organised criminals to launder criminally derived funds | Low (1) | High (3) | Medium (3) | Decrease in likelihood |
| White label providers | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |

### Customer Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
|------|------------|--------|--------------|----------------|
| False or stolen documentation used to bypass controls to launder criminally derived funds | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| Accessibility to multiple remote accounts | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | Decrease in likelihood |
| Customers from high risk or non-cooperative jurisdictions using remote facilities to launder criminally derived funds | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | Decrease in likelihood |
| Customers who appear on international financial sanctions lists laundering criminal funds | Low (1) | High (3) | Medium (3) | No change |
| 'Smurfing' | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | Increase in risk |
| 'Mule' betting accounts | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |
| Politically exposed persons (PEPs) | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (6) | New risk rating |
| Business customers (betting exchange) | Medium (2) | High (3) | High (9) | New risk rating |
| Use of third parties or agents to obscure the source or ownership of money gambled by customers and their identities | High (3) | High (3) | High (9) | No change |

### Means of Payment Vulnerabilities

| Risk | Likelihood | Impact | Overall Risk | Change in Risk |
